> ### 💡 Cryogenic Shock Freezing: The "Bake-to-Order" Strategy
> 
> 
> Private label manufacturing isn't limited to fully baked, shelf-stable grocery boxes. One of the highest-growth segments is the **frozen cookie puck** market (Place-and-Bake). B2B partners can mix and stamp out raw dough portions, passing them directly through liquid-nitrogen spiral blast freezers down to $-30^\circ\text{F}$ ($-34^\circ\text{C}$). This ultra-rapid freezing process prevents large ice crystals from tearing the flour's gluten network. This ensures that when a supermarket in-store bakery, QSR restaurant, or cafe thaws and bakes your frozen pucks months later, the cookie delivers the exact same aroma, lift, and soft, chewy center as a batch mixed fresh from scratch.

